text.section:
The General Assembly finds that the public interest and the interest of policyholders and stockholders may be adversely affected when:
control of an insurer is sought by a person that would use that control adversely to the best interest of policyholders or stockholders;
acquisition of control of an insurer would substantially lessen competition or create a monopoly in the insurance business in the State;
an insurer that is part of an insurance holding company system enters into transactions or relationships with affiliates on terms that are not fair and reasonable; or
an insurer pays to stockholders dividends that jeopardize the financial condition of the insurer.

The purposes of this title include promoting the public interest by:
requiring disclosures in acquisitions or mergers;
requiring disclosures of material transactions, relationships between an insurer and its affiliates, and dividends to stockholders paid by insurers;
requiring disclosures of relevant information about changes in control of insurers; and
establishing penalties for failure to disclose and providing for the disapproval of certain transactions.
